! Getting Started

Follow these simple steps to start tracking your darts competition:

!! Step-by-Step Instructions

# ''Add Players'': Enter player names in the text field and click "Add Player"
# ''Start Game'': Select your game type (501/301/180/Cricket) and click "Start New Game"
# ''Record Scores'': Enter the score thrown and press Enter or click "Record Score"
# ''Track Progress'': Watch the live scoreboard update with current scores and statistics

!! Automatic Features

The scoreboard automatically handles:

* Turn rotation between players
* Win detection when a player reaches exactly 0
* Bust detection (score below 0 or exactly 1 for standard games)
* Game history with timestamps
* Player statistics (games won, average score, best finish)

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

* ''Enter'' - Record the current score
* Standard browser shortcuts for navigation

!! Tips

* Players can be removed by clicking the remove button next to their name
* Use the "Undo" button to correct scoring mistakes
* The history log shows all actions with timestamps
* Statistics are calculated automatically as you play

See [[Game Types]] for specific rules for each game format.
